To reproduce this issue the s3cli was used. To install:

{code}
# yum install golang
{code}

{code}
# go get github.com/pivotal-golang/s3cli
{code}

{code}
# cat config.json
{
  "bucket_name":            "testbucket",
  "credentials_source":     "static",
  "access_key_id":          "AKI...",
  "secret_access_key":      "HIh...",
  "host":                   "s3.domain.goes.here.com",
  "port":                   8773,
  "ssl_verify_peer":        false,
  "use_ssl":                false,
  "signature_version":      "3"
}
{code}

Then to upload a file using multipart:

{code}
# export PATH=$PATH:/root/go/bin
# head -c 10000000 /dev/zero > data.dat
# s3cli -c config.json put data.dat data.dat
{code}

Versions used were s3cli v0.0.54 using aws sdk for go v1.4.18.
